article.description: — Josip Vrankic had 26 points as Santa Clara edged past Pepperdine 86-82 on Saturday.
article.headline: Vrankic leads Santa Clara over Pepperdine 86-82
article.linkText: Vrankic leads Santa Clara over Pepperdine 86-82
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- — Josip Vrankic had 26 points as Santa Clara edged past Pepperdine 86-82 on Saturday. Jalen Williams had 17 points for Santa Clara (10-6, 4-4 West Coast Conference), which ended its four-game home losing streak. Christian Carlyle added 16 points. Giordan Williams had 10 points. Santa Clara totaled 52 second-half points, a season best for the team. Colbey Ross had 26 points and six assists for the Waves (10-9, 6-4). Jan Zidek added 18 points and nine rebounds. Kessler Edwards had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
